For the preprocessing.py you need to download all the parquet files from: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/jeffsinsel/nyc-fhvhv-data as the files are too big to upload to github.
Then put all the parquet files you want into the folder named NYCData.
The python script uses dynamic loading so you can add or remove as many files as you want and the script will generate a sample datbase.
The sample data for weather has already been created.